HEADWORD: Retrocedent
<hw>Re`tro*ced"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>retrocedens</ets>, p. pr.]</ety> <def>Disposed or likely to
retrocede; -- said of diseases which go from one part of the body to
another, as the gout.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

